  <h1 class="my-0">Usability Research Checklist</h1>
  <h5 class="mb-5">A comprehensive list of how to prepare for attacking the great big challenge of usability testing.</h5>
  <p>Conducting your own usability research can seem like an overwhelming task, and while there's certainly a lot of things to cover and get right, it's not insurmountable. This guide is meant to serve as a checklist to make sure you have everything you need to be successful. And, for the things you don't have and can't prepare, you can <a href="/">use MelioraLabs</a>.</p>
  <h2 class="">Overview</h2>
  <ol class="ml-list">
    <li>Gather Resources</li>
    <li>Design the Study</li>
    <li>Prepare for the Study</li>
    <li>Recruit Participants</li>
    <li>Run Study Sessions</li>
    <li>Analyze Results</li>
    <li>Aftermath</li>
  </ol>
  <p>We'll go into detail for each of the above items in their respective post in this series, so let this be your guide. There's a lot more that more goes into designing and running your own usability research than people typically think. Being properly prepared can be the difference between great success and catastrophic failure for your user research. Don't underestimate how much time, energy, and resource setting up a proper usability study takes.</p>

  <h2>What's MelioraLabs?</h2>
  <p>MelioraLabs provides &agrave; la carte usability research facilities and services in NYC. From renting the lab to full service research design and analysis, you decide how much help you need.</p>
  <p>We've run dozens of in-person usability studies for companies from early stage startup all the way to Fortune 500, and everything from half-baked prototypes to mature products with millions of users. This checklist is the result of the lessons we've learned preparing, designing, running, and analyzing lab sessions over the past 7 years.</p>

